To download and extract the data required for this project, click on the   icon on the top of the steps 2 to 6 and 8.  The zip files will contain the following files & folders:


DataSet01.zip

DataSet02.zip

DataSet03.zip

Images.zip

DAX_Measures_Columns.zip

WakeCounty_Real_Estate_Property_Template.zip


Dataset folders - Excel binary  files that have the data from 1990 to 2020 Real Estate Property values:


Datasets\DataSet01

Datasets\DataSet02

Datasets\DataSet03


DAX_Measures_Columns folder - files containing the measures and column formulas. It also includes DAX formula used to create a Date Dimension table and SUMMARIZE COLUMN.

images folder - images that will be used

template - A Power BI template to get you started with the project.


Step 1:  Download the zip file


Step 2:  Extract the zip file to your PC/Notebook


Step 3:  Convert Excel Binary workbook File to Excel Workbook

Due to the size of the file, you will now convert the dataset. Any Microsoft Excel binary workbook file (file extension is .xlsb), will need to be converted to Microsoft Excel .xlsx format).


Open the Excel Binary File using Microsoft Excel. Click on File -> Save As and save it as Excel Workbook, .xlsx
